==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Safranine
<hw>Saf"ra*nine</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called
because used as a substitute for safranin.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An orange-red nitrogenous dyestuff produced artificially by
oxidizing certain aniline derivatives, and used in dyeing silk and wool;
also, any one of the series of which safranine proper is the
type.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

